1. explaing the architecture of nodejs

answer1:

all the synchronous code will be sent to call stack and all the asynchronous code(which require some
time to execute or some APIs to be called)will be sent to node APIs. then all the synchronous code
in call stack will be executed. then asynchronous code is sent to call queue after its waiting tak is
done and then it is sent to call stack and then asynchronous code is also executed.

2. explain the feature of nodejs like non-blocking, synchronous, single threaded.

answer2:

non-blocking--> Non-Blocking means that javascript continues the execution of the synchronous programs
instead of waiting for long I/O operations or any other asynchronous functions.

synchronous--> programs are executed in sequence in javascript and hene it is called synchronous.

single threaded--> this means that only one line of program is executed at a given time in javascript.

